Package gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.merlin.protocol.types

Interface ValueSchema.Visitor<T>

Type Parameters:
T - The return type of the operation represented by this Visitor.
All Known Implementing Classes:
ValueSchema.DefaultVisitor, ValueSchema.OptionalVisitor
Enclosing class:
ValueSchema
public static interface ValueSchema.Visitor<T>
An operation to be performed over the schema described by a ValueSchema. A method must be defined for each kind of data that a ValueSchema may describe. This may be likened to the pattern-matching capability built into languages such as Rust or Haskell. Most clients will prefer to inherit from ValueSchema.DefaultVisitor, which returns `Optional.empty()` for any unimplemented methods.
